Register by July 25thand get 
the early bird registration price forthe9th IEEE-SA Ethernet & IP @ Automotive Technology 
Day <http://go.standards.ieee.org/x0F000000R60D8Y02T2wILN>(E&IP@ATD),24-25 September 2019 in Detroit, Michigan, USA. TheFord Motor Company <http://go.standards.ieee.org/XTD0w3Y08000L02IN006FS0>is our Host. E&IP@ATDis the premier venue for automobile manufacturers, suppliers, semiconductor vendors, tool providers, engineers, scientists, educators, and the media to share ground breaking ideas along with implementation strategies and applications related to Automotive Ethernet Systems.


Presentations will provide insights into the developments, trends, and solutions in the following topics:


	- Current automotive use-cases and future perspectives
	- Ethernet's role to facilitate cloud connectivity
	- Ethernet network design and specification
	- Ethernet requirements for automated driving applications
	- Safety, security, and reliability of Ethernet communications
	- Markets and strategies
	- Tools and tests methods
	- Present and future physical layer and protocol solutions
