View the draft program here <http://go.standards.ieee.org/tTLw0N00FI0D6008Y20006V>!
Sponsor and Exhibitor Opportunities

Platinum and Gold Exhibitor packages have sold out. Silver and Bronze Exhibitor packages are available, as well as sponsorship of a breakfast, coffee break or lunch. You may also purchase a Sponsored Presentation slot to showcase your automotive Ethernet related products and services.

See theExhibitor/Supporter Prospectus <http://go.standards.ieee.org/JY0DFN0W6L0870I0Tw00020>for details.
${Button-Text}  <http://go.standards.ieee.org/dc/TyTOrxmz22SGW307RMIKKL3sHYiUkrhCyzGTTrpxMIQ=/v02I08190TDLFwl6Y00N000>
Contacteipatd-requests@ieee.org <http://go.standards.ieee.org/hDw6Y2Y00F000NT08000L9I>for additional information.
Arrive early and join the IEEE P802.1DG meeting

All are welcome to attend the IEEE 802.1 TSN Interim Plenary Meeting to advance the work ofIEEE P802.1DG (TSN Profile for Automotive In-Vehicle Ethernet Communications) <http://go.standards.ieee.org/dT0Dw6Z80N0LI00Y2a000F0> the day before E&IP@ATD starts.

When: Monday, 23 September 2019
Time: 9 AM  5 PM (arrive by 8:30 AM for security check-in)
Meeting Location: GM Renaissance Center <http://go.standards.ieee.org/E0T0F0wcY0I080NL0102D06>, Tower 100, conference room 21 A27
Meeting Fee: None
Registration: No registration required. Notify Craig Gunther at craiggunther@yahoo.com <http://go.standards.ieee.org/n0Fw01d00N8D0LY0I600T12> by 23 August 2019 to get you on the GM RenCen security list.
